    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nResizing a terminal buffer alters lines in unexpected ways. This occurs when resizing a terminal via a split or when resizing the entire terminal\r\n\r\nSee video demo, below:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/10103049/af03f6ec-ddcd-415d-acce-b47eda25913b\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n- Install Neovim nightly (NVIM v0.10.0-dev-2396+gb4c013c27-dirty, in my case)\r\n- Call `nvim -u NONE`\r\n- Run `:terminal`\r\n- Print something with long lines and then resize the terminal\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nResizing would work without causing blank space which permanently alters the lines\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.10.0-dev-2396+gb4c013c27-dirty\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nyes, vim 9.1\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nCentOS Linux 7 (Core)\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\ngnome or Alacritty (both have the issue)\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "One thing I found that might improve that issue with text truncating is to use a tmux session in the nvim terminal. It's not perfect but it seems to be more forgiving when windows resize. \r\n\r\nMaybe I am imagining things, but I have a demo here you can try: \r\nhttps://gist.github.com/vurentjie/a2f878053e977e35afc5c57ff65f4949 \r\nWhat I do is I create a separate tmux session for each terminal I open in neovim. \r\n",
