            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I was under the impression that https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/2514 was implemented as Neovim 0.10+'s terminal reflow which would handle this case. In which case this seemed to be unintended behavior of the reflow. It'd be nice to know how to reset the view manually because when it breaks like this, the text stays like that and the only recourse is to run the command again. Terminals are a nebulous subject so I could be wrong on where the bug lies exactly but I can say tmux wasn't involved in this but is reproducible there as well.",
